The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Balaji fined 30% of fee

New Delhi: Lakshmipathy Balaji has been fined 30 per cent of his match fee for excessive appealing in the first Test against Pakistan, which ended in Mohali on Saturday. 

Balaji attended a hearing by Match Referee Chris Broad after the match ended in a draw. 

?There is no place for this sort of appealing in international cricket. The player has apologised for his actions,? Broad said in a statement. (Reuters) 




